    <div rend="parallel">
      <lg xml:id="TolE007">
<l>kaṇṇimai noṭiyeṉa vavvē māttirai</l>
<l>nuṇṇiti ṉuṇarntōr kaṇṭa vāṟē</l>
      </lg>
      <lg xml:lang="en">
<l>According to the view of those who have</l>
<l>understood accurately,</l>
<l>one <foreign xml:lang="ta">māttirai</foreign><note place="foot">
              <foreign xml:lang="ta">māttirai</foreign> &gt; Skt <foreign xml:lang="sa">mātrā</foreign>
            </note>
          is the time taken by a wink of the eyes<note place="foot">
              <foreign xml:lang="ta">kaṇṇimai.</foreign>
            </note></l>
<l>[or] a snap of the fingers.<note place="foot"><foreign xml:lang="ta">noṭi.</foreign> This is considered, with some justice, a later, interpolated verse. If so, however, some of the following verses, e.g. 11, should also be considered interpolated.</note></l>
      </lg>
    </div>
